103.8	Guns,_Germs,_and_Steel	Guns, Germs, and Steel	Guns, Germs, and Steel: The Fates of Human Societies is a 1997 book by Jared Diamond, professor of geography and physiology at the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA). In 1998, it won the Pulitzer Prize for general non-fiction and the Aventis Prize for Best Science Book. A documentary based on the book, and produced by the National Geographic Society, was broadcast on PBS in July 2005.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/fc/Ggas_human_soc.jpg/200px-Ggas_human_soc.jpg
